application_type_full: Outline planning permission: Some matters reserved

constraints_details.result: Hinterland Lower Lea Valley including Stratford

description: Outline planning permission (layout  scale  landscaping and appearance reserved) for the demolition of the existing buildings and structures on the site  creation of ten blocks (Blocks A-H and J-K) ranging from 2 to 15 storeys in height  providing the following: re-provision of a new Thames Water Storm Water facility incorporating new underground storm water storage tanks; creation of up to 730 residential units; provision of up to 4 500sqm of commercial floor space to include flexible Class A1  A2  A3  B1  D1 or D2 uses); and construction of a two-form entry primary school (up to 2 190sqm). The proposals also include the creation of areas of public realm and landscaping  and the provision of no more than 15% car parking spaces for the residential units and no more than 20 spaces for the non-residential uses to be provided at basement and ground floor level to include disabled parking spaces and the provision of covered and secure cycle parking.
